article.headline: Arkansas-Pine Bluff 66, Alabama A&M 65
article.story: HUNTSVILLE, Ala. (AP) -- Terrance Calvin scored 11 points, including the game-winning free throw to lead Arkansas-Pine Bluff to a one-point overtime win over Alabama A&M Monday night. The Golden Lions (5-16, 3-7 Southwestern Athletic Conference) took the lead with just over four minutes left in the first half. They stayed ahead until the Bulldogs (7-14, 2-8 SWAC) tied the score on a 3-pointer by Trant Simpson at 55-55 with just three seconds to play in regulation, sending the game into overtime. The Golden Lions shot a lackluster 32.4 percent from the floor during regulation but made up for it by shooting 80 percent in overtime. Calvin was the only double digit scorer for the Lions. Cornelius Hester led the Bulldogs with 19 points. Mickell Gladness chipped in with 15 points and 12 rebounds, while Jonathan Inman and Simpson added 10 points each. Simpson also had 14 assists. Neither team managed more than a two-point lead during overtime, and the score was tied 65-65 with 15 seconds left, when Calvin's final shot sealed the win.
